  <description type="morphology">Plants usually bulbose; bulb coat, when present, membranous. Stems usually stout,
        sparingly branching, not flexuous or twisted, 3–6 dm. Leaves: basal withering, 1–2 dm; blade
        linear, glaucous. Inflorescences subumbellate, 1–4-flowered; bracts opposite pedicel, 4–8
        cm. Flowers erect; perianth open, campanulate; sepals usually with dark red blotch near
        base, lanceolate-ovate, 2–3 cm; petals yellow, often tinged purple in drying, cuneate to
        obovate, 3–5 cm; glands usually ± round, depressed, small, surrounded by conspicuously
        fringed membrane and a few long, yellow hairs, densely covered with slender, unbranched
        hairs; filaments 9–10 mm; anthers yellowish, oblong, 8–10 mm, apex obtuse. Capsules erect,
        lanceoloid-linear, angled, 5–8 cm, apex acuminate. Seeds flat. 2n = ca. 14.</description>
